      <h2>KIC Events Consent & Conduct Policy</h2>
      <p>At KIC Events, consent is the foundation of everything we do. We are committed to maintaining a safe, informed, and welcoming space where all individuals can explore and express themselves freely, without fear of coercion, discrimination, or harm.</p>

      <h3>Consent Statement:</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Consent is SEXY, and Consent is MANDATORY</strong></li>
        <li>We seek enthusiastic consent – clear headed, mutual, informed co-creation of a “YES” without manipulation or coercion.</li>
        <li>It is not an absence of a “NO”.</li>
        <li>No means no. It is a complete sentence, no explanation is needed.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>KIC Safety Guidelines</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>We have event volunteers, Dungeon Monitors (DMs) who wear yellow vests, and Managers on Duty (MOD) who wear a MOD nametag, who work to keep everyone safe.</li>
        <li>DMs and MODs do not see all things all the time, so we are a “see something, say something” group, who share concerns, so they can be addressed.</li>
        <li>We practice Risk Aware Consensual Kink (R.A.C.K) and Safe, Sane, Consensual (S.S.C.) decisions.</li>
        <li>Our safewords are RED and SAFEWORD, and we stop any scene when they are used.</li>
        <li>We do not interrupt people who are in a scene, or doing aftercare (except MODs / DMs), unless there are safety concerns that need immediately addressed.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Community Conduct & Respect</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>We clean up after ourselves after a scene, and after eating or drinking.</li>
        <li>We use barriers on non-play furniture for naked juicy body parts.</li>
        <li>We use barriers to protect the furniture and on the floor when we play with wax.</li>
        <li>We honor posted time limits on play equipment.</li>
        <li>We ask for permission before we touch someone’s body, or someone’s things, unless we have previously negotiated otherwise.</li>
        <li>We respect each others’ privacy at KIC events, and in the world outside our events.</li>
        <li>We dress as “grandma vanilla” when we enter and leave public spaces.</li>
        <li>We do our best to keep airborne irritants (like tobacco smoke or other scents) outside of our events, to help attendees with allergies.</li>
        <li>We do not use phones, cameras, or recording devices unless an area is explicitly posted as being available to do so.</li>
        <li>No alcohol, drugs, illegal substances and/or firearms may be brought to a KIC Event.</li>
        <li>Any activity illegal in the State of Ohio or the US is prohibited at KIC Events. This includes soliciting, prostituting, negotiating payment for play or sexual services, use or sale of substances, etc.</li>
        <li>No firearms or weapons intended to cause physical harm are allowed at KIC events.</li>
        <li>KIC Events will not knowingly allow attendees to attend any function who have been convicted of a violent or sexual crime and/or are registered sex offenders.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>By attending KIC Events, you agree to uphold a culture of consent, respect, and inclusivity. If you have any concerns or need support, reach out to KIC Admin or Staff.</p>

      <h2>KIC Volunteer Code of Conduct</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Be kind, inclusive, and consensual at all times.</li>
        <li>Respect Boundaries – never touch people or their things without clear consent.</li>
        <li>No play while on duty – stay focused, grounded, and present while keeping attendees safe.</li>
        <li>Come ready – don’t show up to a shift late, under the influence, or too worn out to help.</li>
        <li>Everyone’s equal – Leave power dynamics outside of your shift.</li>
        <li>Step up if someone needs help – be proactive and supportive.</li>
        <li>Harassment of any kind won’t be tolerated – whether directed at or from you.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Staff Code of Conduct</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Protect the privacy of information we have access to while working for KIC Events.</li>
        <li><strong>Role Models:</strong> Set the standard for our consent culture; ensure explicit permission for kink and sexual activities.</li>
        <li><strong>High expectations for behavior:</strong> We do not use our roles in KIC to play with attendees or look for our next partner. We understand that we can make imprintable impressions.</li>
        <li><strong>Establish boundaries:</strong> On contentious issues on Fetlife, Discord, or other social media, clarify that you are not posting on behalf of KIC.</li>
        <li><strong>Privileged Information:</strong> Only publicly discuss what KIC has announced publicly.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>KIC Educator Code of Conduct</h2>
      <p>When someone presents for us, we ask them to commit to the following:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Seek and practice informed, affirmative consent in all sexual and kink-related activities.</li>
        <li>There are no pending allegations of consent violations.</li>
        <li>Never been criminally or civilly charged with any violent crime including assault, domestic violence, sexual imposition, rape, battery, manslaughter, or robbery.</li>
        <li>Commit to the <a href="https://www.thekecc.org/educatorVersion.html" target="_blank">Kink Education Code of Conduct (KECC) for Educators</a>.</li>
      </ul>

